What features in the MicroBrowser application did you like most?
column4: Time filter, size/color of each node represents its populatiry and # of answers
column5: I like the overview feature, which provides a big picture between the questions of how they are related.

column2: What features in the MicroBrowser application you did NOT like?
column3: Search reset a lot, double-clicking for detailed view (hard to remember)
column4: I dont quite get how "pattern browser" works.  I think it is very useful but requires sometime to get used to it.
column5: I dont like the detail view, for it does not directly list all answers.  I want to browse all answers at a time and I have to hover my mouse and click on each node.

column2: What new features could be added to improve the MicroBrowser application?
column4:
1. Shapes of answered/unanswered questions may need to be differentiated more instead of "diamond" and "hexagon" images
2. Search by keyword is dynamic and hence it was very slow when I tried it.
3. In discussion panel, only showing thread "title", "keywords" and "answers" should be enough.
column5: I wish there were more inter-question features regarding the smilarities.  this is one thing that web-based systems can not do.
column6: Some of the visualizations is not very intuitive.  I guess there is some scope of improvements to clearly represent different things such as patterns, discussion nodes, etc
